=====================================================================================================================Lesson 13: Page 15-24
I) Fill In the chart :
  # / Dictionary Form / English / Te-form / Potential / Potential Negative 
  1) asobu = To play = Ason De = Aso Beru = Aso BeNai
  2) Oyogu = To swim = Oyoi Te = Oyo Keru = Oyo KeNai 
  3) nomu = to drink = Non De = Nome ru = Nome Nai
  4) yameru = to stop = Yame Te = yamerare ru = yamerare nai 
  5) mo-te kuru = to bring = Mo-te Ki Te = Mo-te Korare ru = Mo-te Korare nai
  6) matsu = to wait = Ma-te = Mate ru = Mate nai
  7) utau = to sing = Uta-te = Utaeru = Utae nai
  8) hashiru = to run = Hashi-te = Hashire ru = Hashire nai
  9) kiku = to ask = Kiite = Kike ru = Kike nai
  10) suru = to do = Shite = Dekiru = Dekinai 
  11) kuru = to come = Kite = Korare ru = Korare nai
  12) kaesu = to return something = Kaeshite = Kaese ru = Kaesenai
  13) kaeru = to return (home) = Kae-Te = Kaere ru = Kaere nai
II) Write 2 things that you can/cannot do, and two things you can/cannot do as a child
  1) A) nihongo ga hanase masu B) sushi ga tsukure masu
  2) A) oyogemasen B) jouzu ni uta ga utae masen
  3) A) konputa ga tsukau shi mashita B) ge-mu ga deki mashita
  4) A) Niku ga taberareru masen deshita B) takusan no hito no maede hanase masen deshita
13-2) I) fill in the second half of the sentences with potential verbs:  
  1) chuugoku ni sunde ita node (speak) = Hanase masu
  2) mizuga kowai node (swim) = oyoge masen
  3) iro iro nako to <thing> ni kyoumi ga naru node, senkou ga (decide) = kimerare masen
  4) kaze o hii te iru node ashita gakou ni (go) = ikemasen
  5) onaka ga sui de iru node, takusan (eat) = taberare masu 
  6) kipun ga warui de kiyou wa (go out) = dekake rare masen
13-2) II) Translate the following sentences :
  1) What kind of songs can you sing? = donna, uta ga utae masu ka? 
  2) Where can I buy cheap clothes = doko de yasui ga kae masu ka? 
  3) I was not able to sleep at all last night = kinou no yoru, zen zen nemurare masen deshita
  4) I am glad because I was able to become a lawyer = pengoshi ni nare de ureshii desu
  5) I was unable to eat eggs when I was a child, but I can eat them now = kodomo no toki, tamago ga taberarre masen deshita ga, ita taberare masu
13-3) I) Complte the sentences using ~Shi :
  1) it is cold + sleepy + okita kunai desu = samu shi nemui shi 
  2) smart + can play the guitar + tanaka san wa jinki ga arimasu = atama ga ii shi gi-ta ga hikeru shi
  3) I have a test + I have to meet the teacher + isogashii desu = tesuto ga aru shi sensei ni awana kiya ike nai shi
  4) often tells a lie + doesn't keep a promise + yamada san ga kirai desu = tuko uso o tsuku shi ya ku so ku o mammoranai shi
  5) I was able to enter university + I have many friends + ima shimewa se desu = dai gaku ni haire ta shi
13-3) II) Answer the questions with a reason using ~Shi :
  1) shourai, nihon de hatara kitai desu ka? = iie、hatara kita kunai desu。nihongo hamuzuka shi ishi、bu-kaha takai shi
  2) anata no machi ga suki desu ka? = iie, kaneda wa kirai desu shi, baka shi, futote shi, furui shi, feminisuto shi, ushi shi, takai shi, fuhai shita shi, ...
  3) natsu to fuyu to dochira ga suki desu ka? = fuyu no hou ga suki desu。yuki ga suki dashi、suki ga de kiru shi。
  4) ima doko ni iki tai desu ka? = toukyou ni iki tai desu。tomodachi ga iru shi、omoshiroi to koro ga takusan aru shi
13-4) I) Describe the pictures with ~sou desu : 
  1) kono sensei hayasa shi sou desu
  2) kono se-ta- haatataka sou desu
  3) kono kodomo hagenki sou desu
  4) kono kare hakara sou desu
  5) kono inu haatama ga yosa sou desu
13-4) II) rephrase the example sentences, using the same pictures :
  1) yasashi sou na sensei desu ne
  2) atataka sou na se-ta desu ne
  3) genki sou na kodomo desu ne
  4) kara sou na karee desu ne
  5) atama ga yosa sou na inu desu ne
